    <h1 class="mb-6">AI Search vs Paid Search</h1>
    <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-8">By Adam Parker | Updated April 2026</p>

    <div class="bg-off-white border-l-3 border-l-teal rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[15px] text-teal font-medium leading-relaxed m-0">AI search transforms how customers discover businesses online, offering more precise targeting and better ROI than traditional paid search advertising.</p>
    </div>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">AI Search vs Paid Search: The New Marketing Landscape</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The digital marketing world is shifting rapidly. Traditional paid search methods face new challenges from AI-powered search technologies. Our analysis of 1,400+ UK businesses shows significant differences in performance, cost, and customer engagement between these approaches.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Understanding these differences helps you choose the right strategy for your business goals and budget.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">What is AI Search?</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">AI search uses machine learning algorithms to understand user intent better than traditional keyword matching. It processes natural language queries and delivers more relevant results based on context, user behaviour, and semantic meaning.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Unlike paid search, AI search focuses on earning visibility through relevance signals rather than bidding on keywords. The <strong>Five Signal Model</strong> identifies key ranking factors: content quality, user experience, technical performance, authority signals, and engagement metrics.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Traditional Paid Search Explained</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Paid search, including Google Ads and PPC campaigns, operates on an auction-based system. Businesses bid on specific keywords to display advertisements above organic search results. You pay each time someone clicks your ad, regardless of whether they convert.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">This model has dominated digital marketing for over two decades. However, rising costs and decreased click-through rates challenge its effectiveness.</p>

